Sentencas: Perovskite oxides (La1-xPrx)(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.8)eFe(0.2)O(3-delta)(x= 0.2,.0.4, 0.6, 0.8) samples were obtained by a solid state-reaction method.
Titulo: Investigation on Oxygen Chemical Diffusion Properties of Perovskite Oxides (La1-xPrx)0.6Sr0.4Co0.8eFe0.2O3-δ

Sentencas: The oxygen chemical diffusion properties of (La1-xPrx)(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.8)eFe(0.2)O(3-delta)were determined by electrical conductivity relaxation technique.
Titulo: Investigation on Oxygen Chemical Diffusion Properties of Perovskite Oxides (La1-xPrx)0.6Sr0.4Co0.8eFe0.2O3-δ

Sentencas: The results show that the conductivity of (La1-xPrx)(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.8)eFe(0.2)O(3-delta) increases with increasing of oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: Investigation on Oxygen Chemical Diffusion Properties of Perovskite Oxides (La1-xPrx)0.6Sr0.4Co0.8eFe0.2O3-δ

Sentencas: The (La1-xPrx)(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.8)eFe(0.2)O(3-delta) samples have higher oxygen chemical diffusion coefficients, which decrease linearly with the decreasing of temperature and increasing of Pr content.
Titulo: Investigation on Oxygen Chemical Diffusion Properties of Perovskite Oxides (La1-xPrx)0.6Sr0.4Co0.8eFe0.2O3-δ

Sentencas: The oxygen chemical diffusion coefficients D-chem remains fairly constant at high Po-2.
Titulo: Investigation on Oxygen Chemical Diffusion Properties of Perovskite Oxides (La1-xPrx)0.6Sr0.4Co0.8eFe0.2O3-δ

Sentencas: The oxygen chemical diffusion coefficient is highest at x=0.2, 9.41x 10(-5) cm(2).s(-1) at 700 degrees C, and the material is comparatively potential cathodes material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Titulo: Investigation on Oxygen Chemical Diffusion Properties of Perovskite Oxides (La1-xPrx)0.6Sr0.4Co0.8eFe0.2O3-δ
